article.description: — Isaac Mushila had 27 points and 14 rebounds as Texas A&M-Corpus Christi extended its win streak to seven games, beating Texas Rio Grande Valley 75-69 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Texas A&M-CC defeats Texas Rio Grande Valley 75-69
article.linkText: Texas A&M-CC defeats Texas Rio Grande Valley 75-69
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas -- — Isaac Mushila had 27 points and 14 rebounds as Texas A&M-Corpus Christi extended its win streak to seven games, beating Texas Rio Grande Valley 75-69 on Wednesday night. Simeon Fryer had 18 points for Texas A&M-Corpus Christi (8-1). Jalen Jackson added 14 points. De'Lazarus Keys had seven rebounds. Myles Smith, who was second on the Islanders in scoring with 10 points per game, had only five points on 2-of-11 shooting. Ricky Nelson had 17 points for the Vaqueros (4-6), whose losing streak stretched to four games. Justin Johnson added 15 points. He also had eight turnovers but only two assists. Xavier Johnson had 12 points. RayQuan Taylor had 11 points and 19 rebounds. The Islanders improve to 2-0 against the Vaqueros this season. Texas A&M-Corpus Christi defeated Texas Rio Grande Valley 83-77 last Wednesday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
